article.headline: Drexel 88, James Madison 60
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Jeremiah King scored 22 points and Sean Brooks had 20 to lead Drexel to an 88-60 victory over James Madison on Saturday. Phil Goss added 14 points and Dominick Majia had 12 for the Dragons (10-7, 6-3 Colonial Athletic Association), who led 37-28 at the half and won their sixth out of the last seven contests. Ray Barbosa scored 28 points for James Madison (4-13, 2-7), which cut the lead to seven points early in the second half before a 22-4 Drexel run put the game out of reach. The Dragons shot a season-high 58 percent in the game, including 69 percent in the second half, made 23 of 27 free throws, and outrebounded James Madison 32-17. The Dukes managed only about 41 percent for the game.
